snippet: Kenneth T. Cuccinelli II, the Virginia attorney general, did not violate ethics rules in failing to disclose some $5,100 in gifts from a corporate executive, an independent investigator said Thursday.
abstract: Kenneth T. Cuccinelli II, the Virginia attorney general, did not violate ethics rules in failing to disclose some $5,100 in gifts from a corporate executive, an independent investigator said Thursday.

headline.main: Investigators Clear Virginia's Cuccinelli in Ethics Probe
